JOHANNESBURG - Just a day after the SABC's contentious retrenchment process wrapped up, live broadcasts on some of its radio stations were interrupted on Thursday morning, with the broadcaster blaming a power outage. The break in transmission comes just hours after the emotional exit of hundreds of employees. READ: SABC retrenchments brings newsreader to tears on air They were retrenched after the board announced last year that it would undergo a restructuring process to try and trim its R2.4 billion annual salary bill. The stations, which were offline for just under an hour, appeared to be back on air now. Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.